headline: GE Aerospace Price Targets Suggest a Record High Is Coming. How That’s Possible.
summary: After  GE Aerospace  produced “blowout” second-quarter results, Wall Street reacted by raising its targets for the stock price, suggesting shares could soon reach a record high.  Wall Street was looking for operating profit of $2.1 billion and earnings per share of $1.43 on sales of $9.6 billion, according to FactSet.  Management now expects 2025 operating profit of between $8.2 billion and $8.5 billion, up from a prior range of $7.8 billion to $8.2 billion.
